The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 KSL and Industries has announced spilt of its equity shares with face value of Rs10 each to shares with face value of Rs 4 each with effect from September 23. This means every two equity shares of Rs 10 each will be split into five equity shares of Rs 4 each. A resolution to this effect was approved at the recently held extra ordinary general meeting of the company. KSL, an integrated textile mill that has recently forayed into realty, has a share capital of Rs 31.80 crore. 

 Alps Industries will issue 41.5 lakh equity shares of Rs 10 each for cash at a premium of Rs 110 per share for the public from September 20. The issue aims to mop up Rs 49.8 crore. The net offering to the public will be of 26.5 lakh shares. The proceeds from the issue would be used in setting up of a 50.161-tonne per day spinning unit. It closes on September 23. 

 Kotak SEAF India Fund, a venture capital fund, has invested Rs 25 crore in Four Soft Limited. The private equity fund of Kotak Mahindra Bank has bought 39,49,447 equity Shares of Rs 5 each at a premium of Rs 58.30 per share. The Investment by the fund comes at a time when Four Soft is consolidating its businesses for higher growth. 

 Rajesh Exports has bagged an order worth Rs 124 crore of 22-carat designer jewellery from the Singapore-based Gold Star Jewellery. The consignment will be executed at the company?s manufacturing facility in Bangalore, which is the world?s largest jewellery manufacturing facility spread over 12 acres with a built-up area of 5 lakh sq ft. 

 Caritor has won a major contract from Tantia Constructions for implementing its enterprise resource planning solutions. Under the agreement, Caritor will provide an integrated backbone for the Tantia?s projects covering the materials management, financial and management accounting, project planning and monitoring. 

 Juniper Networks has launched Secure Access 6000 SP for network-based SSL VPN managed services. The service providers with this can offer remote and extranet access to customers.

